From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Subject: cameraisp: WPE/DIP probe fixes for Volla X23 native boot

The vidofnir mt6789.dts has DT issues for WPE+DIP camera subsystems:
- wpe_a@15011000 / wpe_b@15811000: bare nodes (compatible/reg/interrupts only)
- imgsys_config@15020000: mediatek,larb has only 1 phandle but driver expects 2

Original behaviour deadlocks PID 1 (insmod) and trips SoC watchdog ~30s later.

Fixes:

1. WPE_probe + DIP_probe: early-return -ENODEV when mediatek,larb is absent.
   Avoids pm_runtime_enable + of_find_device_by_node(NULL) on bare DT nodes
   (of_find_device_by_node(NULL) returns a NON-NULL garbage pointer that
   the WARN_ON check fails to catch).

2. DIP_probe: stop dereferencing NULL phandles.  Original code passes
   node_larb9/11 directly to of_find_device_by_node even when of_parse_phandle
   returned NULL.  Add NULL-checks; leave dip_devs->larb11 as NULL — its
   only consumer is conditional on DIP_IMG_MFB_DIP / DIP_IMG_DIP2 clocks
   being present, which they aren't on this device.

The earlier VOLLAX23_BISECT `#if 0` of cmdqCoreRegisterCB + register_pm_notifier
in WPE_Init / DIP_Init has been REMOVED — it let modules insmod without hanging,
but the runtime DIP ioctls (set tpipe mem info, setLCE_D1, etc.) then ran without
the cmdq/pm hooks registered and reliably crashed the SoC.  UBports loads these
modules late (systemd-modules-load.service post-userspace) so cmdq is already
fully initialized when these calls run.  The matching change is to defer
camera_wpe_isp6s + camera_dip_isp6s insmod out of OHOS pre-init into a later
boot stage (see init.x23.cfg).

Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>

--- a/drivers/misc/mediatek/cameraisp/wpe/isp_6s/camera_wpe.c	2026-05-21 15:55:27.544631127 +0000
+++ b/drivers/misc/mediatek/cameraisp/wpe/isp_6s/camera_wpe.c	2026-05-21 16:44:52.672925985 +0000
@@ -5113,6 +5113,19 @@
 
 	LOG_INF("- E. WPE driver probe.");
 
+	/*
+	 * Volla X23: wpe_a/wpe_b DT nodes are bare (no mediatek,larb).
+	 * The original probe calls pm_runtime_enable + of_find_device_by_
+	 * node(NULL) BEFORE the bail-out, which deadlocks PID 1 (insmod)
+	 * and trips the SoC watchdog.  Bail cleanly here.
+	 */
+	if (pDev && pDev->dev.of_node &&
+	    !of_property_read_bool(pDev->dev.of_node, "mediatek,larb")) {
+		dev_info(&pDev->dev,
+			 "WPE: bare DT node (no mediatek,larb), skipping probe\n");
+		return -ENODEV;
+	}
+
 	/* Check platform_device parameters */
 #ifdef CONFIG_OF
 
--- a/drivers/misc/mediatek/cameraisp/dip/isp_6s/camera_dip.c	2026-05-21 15:55:27.548631206 +0000
+++ b/drivers/misc/mediatek/cameraisp/dip/isp_6s/camera_dip.c	2026-05-21 16:44:52.676926061 +0000
@@ -7240,6 +7240,19 @@
 #endif
 
 	LOG_INF("- E. DIP driver probe. nr_dip_devs : %d.\n", nr_dip_devs);
+
+	/*
+	 * Volla X23: dip_a0 DT node is bare (no mediatek,larb).  The
+	 * original probe LOG_INFs the missing phandle but keeps going,
+	 * calling of_find_device_by_node(NULL) which returns a garbage
+	 * non-NULL pointer.  Bail cleanly here.
+	 */
+	if (pDev && pDev->dev.of_node &&
+	    !of_property_read_bool(pDev->dev.of_node, "mediatek,larb")) {
+		LOG_INF("DIP: bare DT node (no mediatek,larb), skipping probe\n");
+		return -ENODEV;
+	}
+
 	max_tdr_no = 0;
 	mtk_dip_count = 1;
 	G_u4DipEnClkCnt = 0;
@@ -7284,17 +7297,19 @@
 		if (!node_larb9 || !node_larb11)
 			LOG_INF("no get node_larb9 or larb11\n");
 
-		pdev_larb9 = of_find_device_by_node(node_larb9);
-		pdev_larb11 = of_find_device_by_node(node_larb11);
-		if (WARN_ON(!pdev_larb9) || WARN_ON(!pdev_larb11)) {
-			of_node_put(node_larb9);
-			of_node_put(node_larb11);
-			return -EINVAL;
-		}
-		of_node_put(node_larb9);
-		of_node_put(node_larb11);
-		dip_devs->larb9 = &pdev_larb9->dev;
-		dip_devs->larb11 = &pdev_larb11->dev;
+		/*
+		 * VOLLAX23: of_find_device_by_node(NULL) returns a non-NULL
+		 * garbage pointer (matches non-DT platform devices), so we
+		 * must NULL-check the original node here.  Don't bail — just
+		 * leave larb9/11 as NULL; the HAL only opens /dev/camera-dip
+		 * for ioctls that don't follow the larb pointers.
+		 */
+		pdev_larb9  = node_larb9  ? of_find_device_by_node(node_larb9)  : NULL;
+		pdev_larb11 = node_larb11 ? of_find_device_by_node(node_larb11) : NULL;
+		if (node_larb9)  of_node_put(node_larb9);
+		if (node_larb11) of_node_put(node_larb11);
+		dip_devs->larb9  = pdev_larb9  ? &pdev_larb9->dev  : NULL;
+		dip_devs->larb11 = pdev_larb11 ? &pdev_larb11->dev : NULL;
 	}
 
 #if defined(CONFIG_MTK_IOMMU_PGTABLE_EXT) && \
